    "summary": "Hello! I'm Richelle Dsouza, a driven advocate for sustainability with a budding expertise and keen interest in data-driven insights, project management, and leadership. Pursuing a Bachelor's Degree in Global Sustainability Sciences at Utrecht University, I aspire to contribute my skills and enthusiasm to impactful sustainability projects \ud83c\udf0e\ud83c\udf43\n\nChallenges fuel my growth. As Head of Fundraising for the UNICEF student team Utrecht, I raised \u20ac1,033.52 for Ivory Coast Building Blocks project. Founder of the Student Environmental Association, I led eco-friendly initiatives and fundraised for WWF, through the 1st ever 'Climate Change Conference'. In my role as Volunteer Festival Liaison Manager at Conscious Festival-'Green is the New Black,' I navigated the dynamic festival landscape, ensuring smooth operations and handling sales accounts and merchandise\u00a0with\u00a0finesse \ud83d\udcaa\ud83d\udcb8\n\nI thrive on creativity. Working on 'Liquid Amenities' project during Covid-19 as an intern, I drafted sustainable action plans and proposals. As Secretary of Charity Committee (STORM with Oaesbos), I managed communications and raised \u20ac4,787.20 for conservation of forests in Costa rica\ud83c\udf33\ud83e\udd8c\n\nI'm seeking new opportunities to drive positive change. If your organization shares my passion for sustainability, let's connect and make a greener tomorrow together \u2728\ud83c\udf31\ud83c\udf0a",
